com.camsolute.code.camp.lib.models

Class CampInstanceDao

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camsolute.code.camp.lib.models.CampInstanceDao
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasResultSetToInstance<CampInstance>, TableDaoInterface, CampInstanceDaoInterface

    public class CampInstanceDao
extends java.lang.Object
implements CampInstanceDaoInterface, HasResultSetToInstance<CampInstance>, TableDaoInterface
    The CampInstance object encapsulates a unique temporal aspect of an object instance together with its process related status aspects at a point in its life cycle. The temporal aspect of an object instance is denoted by a unique identifier - the objects InstanceId - which changes each time an object is modified or changes state and is then persisted. the process status aspect is relevant to any process connected to a business object. A CampInstance object therefore provides access to a representation of an object at the time it was persisted. In order to be able to navigate the various temporal aspects of an object the CampInstance object contains an object's initial and current InstanceId.
    Author:
    Christopher Campbell
